<img src="http://prod.homepage.dk/pics/1106bs.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukaantukii.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kaantukii</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/24/02 10:52:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22435.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> SZ is fun!</span><hr size=1> I am done with Bluebie servers.  As a 3 year EQ player I have gone Red.  Its the best!  Why?  Read on.<br>
  The other night I dusted off my old rogue on Lanys to chat with Guildmates and the situation was laughable.  I no sooner sit down for a bull session when someone shouts<br>
  &quot;Attention Plz ppl move away from the landing zone at port. you just cost me 400 hp&quot; yayaya whine whine.  This went on for awhile as soon the whole zone join in to condemn the inconsiderate actions of others.<br>
  On sullon sitting on a landing might be a good tactic to get on jump on a wizzy or such.  But more than likely the whiner would have gotten a deserved blade in his back.  Then he could go back to his bluebie server and whine about the inconsiderate actions of others.<br>
  Anyway, being on Sullon is being challenged every minute your in the game.  The population is low, meeting someone is a cause to share an ale and compare notes on Evils, and Allys.  Higher levels are watching out for their younger brothers and sisters, and maybe have a gift to give.  A group of greens can stalk and kill that higher red punk.  Trains are in the form of red con bards and such crossing the zone and leaving tombstones behind.  There are no auctions, deals really are carried out in the back alleys.  Bandages really can save your life, even during battle.  Tradeskills are useful and welcomed.  NO TWINKS. <br>
  To be a part of a PVP battle on Sullon is chaotic at best,  the adrenaline rush, tense, scary!  To watch a battle, its as graceful as ice skaters going for Olympic Gold.  <br>
